<br>
<br>
An AA that allows the bard to buff his target with group songs. A second rank in the skill that buffs the target group would be fun too. &lt;clickable&gt;<br>
<br>
<br>
Mass group buff type AA. I'm thinking click this on, then the next group song hits all within range, and that song lasts for 1 min (or whatever -- much longer than normal group songs, but still reasonably short) on all within range.  &lt;clickable&gt;<br>
<br>
<br>
An AA that MEGA buffs a targeted character for a short period of time. Something like the druid wrath of the wild. Suggestions include: buff a caster and have it double their spell damage, or buff a melee and have it double their melee damage, or buff a warrior/knight and double their AC. Heck all the above. Use your imagination on this... I just think it would be neat too REALLY super buff one other character for a short period of time. Bellow of inspiration or something. &lt;clickable&gt;<br>
<br>
<br>
An AA that raises (or eliminates) the song modifier cap for a short period of time. &lt;clickable&gt;<br>
<br>
<br>
AA that works like cannibalization. Something that turns health into mana, with a re-use timer. &lt;clickable&gt;<br>
<br>
<br>
AA that works like an eye of zomm... but creates an illusion of the bard. &lt;clickable&gt;<br>
<br>
<br>
AA that eliminates the need for line of sight for detrimental effects (they can hear me even if they cannot see me). &lt;could be clickable with a re-use timer&gt;<br>
<br>
<br>
I would like to see bards get more use out of disciplines (hey disciplines are clickable). The limit on our current disciplines is the re-use time, not endurance. I would like bards to have Four new disciples that each raise one song modifier (and cap) some amount (0.5), have short re-use timers but significant endurance cost. This would introduce a new element of strategy. Please do not nerf puretone for this. Please make the disciplines easy to obtain.<br>
